  "body": "###### Info\r\n\r\n- **Version**: MyEtherWallet v6.7.5\r\n- **Browser**: Firefox\r\n- **OS**: Linux\r\n- **Page Url**: N/A\r\n\r\n###### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Initiated an offline transaction through MyEtherWallet (MEW).\r\n2. Manually set the gas price to 22 Gwei during the transaction.\r\n3. Generated the transaction.\r\n\r\n###### What do you expect to happen?\r\n\r\nI expect the generated transaction to reflect the manually set gas price of 22 Gwei accurately.\r\n\r\n###### What happens instead?\r\n\r\nThe generated transaction displays a gas price of 22000000000, which is significantly higher than the intended 22 Gwei, raising concerns about its accuracy and potential overpayment.\r\n\r\n###### Screenshot\r\n\r\n![unnamed](https://github.com/MyEtherWallet/MyEtherWallet/assets/8014935/6cc34acd-f9c9-4422-b231-107e3614ad9c)\r\n",
